<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Interruptedexception on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/interruptedexception/</link><description>Recent content in Interruptedexception on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/interruptedexception/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Java InterruptedException — Thread Interrupt Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/interruptedexception/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/interruptedexception/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="interruptedexception--thread-interrupt-fix"&gt;InterruptedException — Thread Interrupt Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;code&gt;InterruptedException&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when a thread is interrupted while it is sleeping, waiting, or otherwise blocked in an interruptible operation. It is a checked exception and signals that another thread has requested the current thread to stop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exception is part of Java&amp;rsquo;s concurrency API. It fires when &lt;code&gt;Thread.interrupt()&lt;/code&gt; is called on a thread that is in one of these states:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Thread.sleep()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Object.wait()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Thread.join()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Blocking &lt;code&gt;I/O&lt;/code&gt; (e.g., &lt;code&gt;InputStream.read()&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Lock.lockInterruptibly()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Future.get()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The critical detail: &lt;strong&gt;catching and swallowing &lt;code&gt;InterruptedException&lt;/code&gt; clears the interrupt flag&lt;/strong&gt;, silently preventing higher-level code from detecting the interrupt.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Kotlin InterruptedException — Thread Interrupt Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/interrupted/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/interrupted/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="interruptedexception--thread-interrupt-fix"&gt;InterruptedException — Thread Interrupt Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;code&gt;InterruptedException&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when a thread is interrupted while it&amp;rsquo;s in a blocking operation like &lt;code&gt;Thread.sleep()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;wait()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;join()&lt;/code&gt;, or I/O operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Java/Kotlin threads can be interrupted to signal them to stop. When a blocking operation detects the interrupt, it throws &lt;code&gt;InterruptedException&lt;/code&gt; and clears the interrupt status. This is a checked exception in Java.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thread.sleep interrupted&lt;/strong&gt; — another thread calls &lt;code&gt;thread.interrupt()&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blocking I/O interrupted&lt;/strong&gt; — reading from stream while thread is interrupted.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lock acquisition interrupted&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;Lock.lockInterruptibly()&lt;/code&gt; during interruption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coroutine cancellation&lt;/strong&gt; — coroutines use &lt;code&gt;InterruptedException&lt;/code&gt; internally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Thread.sleep interrupted
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; thread = Thread {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;.sleep(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10000&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// InterruptedException if interrupted
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Done sleeping&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (e: InterruptedException) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Sleep interrupted&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;thread.start()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;thread.interrupt() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Causes InterruptedException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Blocking in coroutine scope
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; job = launch {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;.sleep(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5000&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Blocks thread, may throw InterruptedException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Waiting on condition
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; lock = Any()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;synchronized(lock) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; lock.wait() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// InterruptedException if interrupted while waiting
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Blocking queue
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; queue = LinkedBlockingQueue&amp;lt;String&amp;gt;()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;queue.take() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// InterruptedException if interrupted while waiting
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-handle-interruptedexception-properly"&gt;Fix 1: Handle InterruptedException properly&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong — swallowing interrupt
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;.sleep(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (e: InterruptedException) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Ignoring interrupt
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct — restore interrupt status
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;.sleep(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (e: InterruptedException) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;.currentThread().interrupt() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Restore interrupt status
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Interrupted, cleaning up...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-cancellation-aware-operations-in-coroutines"&gt;Fix 2: Use cancellation-aware operations in coroutines&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong — Thread.sleep in coroutine (blocks thread)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; job = launch {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;.sleep(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5000&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct — use delay (cancellable)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; job = launch {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; delay(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5000&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Responds to coroutine cancellation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-check-interrupt-status-in-loops"&gt;Fix 3: Check interrupt status in loops&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong — doesn&amp;#39;t check for interruption
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; processItem()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct — check interrupt status
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (!&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;.currentThread().isInterrupted) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; processItem()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-interruptible-channels"&gt;Fix 4: Use interruptible channels&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong — blocking channel operation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; channel = Channel&amp;lt;Int&amp;gt;()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; value = channel.receive() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// May block indefinitely
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct — with timeout
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; value = withTimeoutOrNull(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5000&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; channel.receive()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; kotlin.concurrent.thread
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; worker = thread {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Working...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;.sleep(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2000&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Done&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (e: InterruptedException) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Worker interrupted&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;.currentThread().interrupt()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;.sleep(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;500&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Interrupting worker...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; worker.interrupt()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; worker.join()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; println(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Main done&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/cancellation-exception/"&gt;CancellationException&lt;/a&gt; — coroutine cancellation mechanism.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/runtime-exception/"&gt;ThreadDeath&lt;/a&gt; — thread terminated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/io-exception/"&gt;IOException&lt;/a&gt; — blocking I/O operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>